function maxSubarraySumWithDistinctElements(nums, k) {
    let max_sum = 0, window_sum = 0;
    let freq_map = new Map();

    for (let i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
        freq_map.set(nums[i], (freq_map.get(nums[i]) || 0) + 1);
        window_sum += nums[i];
        if (i >= k) {
            freq_map.set(nums[i - k], freq_map.get(nums[i - k]) - 1);
            window_sum -= nums[i - k];
        }
        if (i >= k - 1) {
            let is_distinct = true;
            for (let value of freq_map.values()) {
                if (value > 1) {
                    is_distinct = false;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if (is_distinct) {
                max_sum = Math.max(max_sum, window_sum);
            }
        }
    }
    return max_sum;
}
```

    For each language implementation, the algorithm works as follows:
1. Initialize a frequency map to keep track of the number of occurrences of each element in the current window of `k` elements.
2. Iterate through the `nums` array, updating the frequency map and current `window_sum` at each step.
3. If the current index is greater than or equal to `k`, remove the oldest element from the frequency map and `window_sum` to maintain a sliding window of size `k`.
4. If the current index is greater than or equal to `k - 1`, check if all elements in the sliding window are distinct by ensuring no values in the frequency map are greater than 1.
5. If the elements in the sliding window are distinct, update `max_sum` to be the maximum of the current `max_sum` and `window_sum`.
6. After iteration is complete, return the `max_sum`.

This algorithm runs in O(n) time complexity as we iterate through the `nums` array once, and it only checks the values of elements in the frequency map at each step. The space complexity is also O(n) since we may need to store a frequency map for all distinct elements in the `nums` array.

